.TH "DOMQUAD.FROMRECT_STATIC" "3JS" "October 27, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
DOMQuad.fromRect_static \- DOMQuad: fromRect() static method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]fromRect()\f[B]\f[R] static method of the
\f[CR]DOMQuad\f[R] interface returns a new \f[CR]DOMQuad\f[R] object
based on the provided set of coordinates in the shape of a
\f[CR]DOMRect\f[R] object.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
DOMQuad.fromRect()
DOMQuad.fromRect(rect)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]rect\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMRect\f[R], \f[CR]DOMRectReadOnly\f[R], or an object with the
same properties.
All properties default to \f[CR]0\f[R].
The properties are:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]x\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The x coordinate of the rectangle\(cqs origin (top\-left corner).
.TP
\f[B]y\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The y coordinate of the rectangle\(cqs origin (top\-left corner).
.TP
\f[B]width\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The width of the rectangle.
.TP
\f[B]height\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The height of the rectangle.
.RE
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]DOMQuad\f[R] object.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Creating a rectangular quad
This example creates a \f[CR]DOMQuad\f[R] from scratch that happens to
be rectangular.
Using \f[CR]fromRect()\f[R] is more convenient than using the
\f[CR]DOMQuad()\f[R] constructor.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] quad = DOMQuad.fromRect({ x: 10, y: 20, width: 100, height: 50 });

console.log(quad.p1); \f[I]// DOMPoint {x: 10, y: 20, z: 0, w: 1}\f[R]
console.log(quad.p2); \f[I]// DOMPoint {x: 110, y: 20, z: 0, w: 1}\f[R]
console.log(quad.p3); \f[I]// DOMPoint {x: 110, y: 70, z: 0, w: 1}\f[R]
console.log(quad.p4); \f[I]// DOMPoint {x: 10, y: 70, z: 0, w: 1}\f[R]
.EE
.SS Creating a quad from DOMRect
This example shows how to create a \f[CR]DOMQuad\f[R] from a
\f[CR]DOMRect\f[R] object.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] domRect = \f[B]new\f[R] DOMRect(50, 60, 200, 100);
\f[B]const\f[R] quad = DOMQuad.fromRect(domRect);

console.log(quad.p1); \f[I]// DOMPoint {x: 50, y: 60, z: 0, w: 1}\f[R]
console.log(quad.p2); \f[I]// DOMPoint {x: 250, y: 60, z: 0, w: 1}\f[R]
console.log(quad.p3); \f[I]// DOMPoint {x: 250, y: 160, z: 0, w: 1}\f[R]
console.log(quad.p4); \f[I]// DOMPoint {x: 50, y: 160, z: 0, w: 1}\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]DOMQuad()\f[R] constructor
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]DOMRect\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]DOMPoint\f[R]
